    "To ensure comparability with the tree-based model feature importances, the average coefficients were also normalized.",
    "Each horizontal bar in the figure shows Here, β j is the mean coefficient estimate for feature j across splits or runs, and SD(β j) is the standard deviation of these mean estimates.",
    "The CI illustrates the uncertainty in the estimated effect size of each feature.Figures 5 and 6 display the mean feature importance scores I j obtained from the Random Forest and XGBoost model's feature_importances_ attribute respectively.",
    "This attribute measures the contribution of each feature j to the model's predictive power-total variance reduction across trees for Random Forest, and gain (i.e., improvement in regression loss) for XGBoost.",
    "Importance values are averaged over all training splits, with only features exceeding 1% importance shown."
